The universal property of the coequalizer Y\xrightarrow {e} E of a
  diagram X\overset {f,g}{\rightrightarrows }Y is that, for any object Z equipped with
  a morphismY\xrightarrow {d} Z such that df = dg, there exists a unique
  factorization E\to  Z of d: 




